comments: Connaughton (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Wiggins (GSW).
Looney (GSW) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Holiday (MIL) that affects his ability to follow-through naturally on his driving shot attempt.
Middleton (MIL) is in the paint and actively guarding an opponent within three seconds.
Connaughton (MIL) has one arm collapsed into his body and the other in a vertical position when he absorbs the contact from Bazemore (GSW) on his driving shot attempt.
Lopez (MIL) does not make contact with the ball while it rolls around in the imaginary cylinder and before it is scored.
Middleton (MIL) makes marginal contact to Curry's (GSW) front as he releases away from the contact at the end of his drive.
Middleton (MIL) makes marginal contact to Curry's (GSW) front as he releases away from the contact on his step back move.

Curry (GSW) makes contact with Middleton's (MIL) leg after the release, which affects his ability to follow-through naturally on his jump shot attempt. The Replay Center confirms the call on the court of a common foul.
Connaughton (MIL) stays attached to Bazemore (GSW) with a resting forearm on his body that he does not extend or deliver contact with on the driving shot attempt. Lopez (MIL) cleanly blocks the shot.
The Replay Center confirmed  that Lopez (MIL) touched the ball before it has reached its apex and is on its way down, making the challenge successful.
During the rebound, Looney (GSW) and Lopez (MIL) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Holiday (MIL) makes clean ball contact to tap the rebound away from Bazemore (GSW).
Lopez (MIL) makes contact with Oubre Jr.'s (GSW) arm after the release, which affects his ability to follow-through naturally on his shot near the rim.
Wiggins (GSW) legally contests and cleanly blocks Middleton's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Connaughton (MIL) secures the rebound and turns his body while airborne to attempt the shot.  Bazemore (GSW) extends his hand forward and cleanly blocks the put back shot attempt.
During the rebound, Lopez (MIL) and Looney (GSW) mutually engage and any contact as they both pursue the loose ball is deemed marginal.
